      "note_no": "14",
      "note": "I.e., the message of which the doctrine of God's oneness and uniqueness is the focal point. By the use of the word \"doubt\" (rayb), this passage is meant to recall the opening sentence of this surah : \"This divine writ - let there be no doubt about it ...\", etc. The gradualness of revelation is implied in the grammatical form nazzalna - which is important in this context inasmuch as the opponents of the Prophet argued that the Qur'an could not be of divine origin because it was being revealed gradually, and not in one piece (Zamakhshari)."
